org.conqat.lib.commons.cache4j

Class CacheFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.conqat.lib.commons.cache4j.CacheFactory

  • public class CacheFactory
extends java.lang.Object
    The central factory used for managing and creating caches. The type of cache is determined based on the name of the cache (possibly based on the class name). For this, there is a list of rules with regular expressions. The first rule, whose expression matches the name is used to create the cache. If no rule matches, the default rule is used.

    The rules can also be loaded from a configuration file, where each line contains a rule (or a comment starting with '#'). Each rule has the format "PATTERN -> THREAD:STRATEGY:PARAMETER", where PATTERN is the pattern used for matching, THREAD is a constant from ECacheThreadSupport, STRATEGY is a constant from ECachingStrategy, and PARAMETER is a parameter for the strategy.

    This factory also manages links to all caches created (via this factory). These links are used for generating statistics. To not avoid garbage collection of caches (e.g. when many caches are created only temporarily), we use weak references which to not hinder the GC from collecting a cache.
